Managing Director


Biography
Cliff has been with Sigma Partners for over 25 years, joining the firm in 1985. Cliff has worked with multiple portfolio companies and combines his prior experience as a consultant and engineer to provide counsel to entrepreneurs on how to build strong businesses. Cliff has been involved with investments in a variety of sectors, focused largely on business software applications, storage, and semiconductor capital equipment.
Background
Prior to Sigma, Cliff was with Cresap, McCormick and Paget, a general management consulting firm, where he worked with senior management teams of domestic and international companies, addressing operational and strategic issues. Previously, he worked at American Pacific Corporation, an AMEX-listed company, where he performed marketing and financial studies as Assistant to the President. Early in his career, Cliff was with 3M Corporation, where he was a member of an in-house start-up team that developed and brought to market several computer storage peripheral products.
Education
Cliff graduated with a B.S. degree in engineering from California Polytechnic State University. He also has an M.B.A. from Stanford University Graduate School of Business.
